ArrayList

import java.util.ArrayList;

The three forms to create an ArrayList:
ArrayList list1 = new ArrayList();
ArrayList list2 = new ArrayList(10);
ArrayList list3 = new ArrayList(list2);
ArrayList<String> list4 = new ArrayList<String>(); -> java5 introduced generics
ArrayList<String> list5 = new ArrayList<>(); -> java7
List<String> list6 = new ArrayList<>();
ArrayList<String> list7 = new List<>(); // DOES NOT COMPILE

Inteface List, an ArrayList implements List, so ArrayList is a List

ArrayList Methods

add() -> add an element in the list
boolean add(E element)
void add(int index, E element)

remove() -> remove the list element
boolean remove(Object object)
E remove(int index)

set() -> override the list element
E set(int index, E newElement)

isEmpty() -> return if the list are empty

size() -> return the size of the list, similar to length()

clear() -> remove/discard all elements from the list

contains() -> check if certain value is in ArrayList
boolean contains(Object object)

equals() -> compare if two lists have the same elements at the same order